A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Code Section 20-2-149.4 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
2 financial literacy instruction and curriculum, so as to require the State Board of Education
3 to adopt content standards for instruction in financial literacy and money management for
4 grades four and five; to require local boards of education to provide instruction in financial
5 literacy and money management in grades four and five; to provide for related matters; to
6 repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
7 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
8 SECTION 1.
9 Code Section 20-2-149.4 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to financial
10 literacy instruction and curriculum, is amended by adding a new subsection to read as
11 follows:
12 "(c)(1) No later than January 1, 2026, the State Board of Education shall adopt content
13 standards for instruction in financial literacy and money management to be completed by
14 students in grades four and five.
